    dc:title "Ride on female for “ prima nocta ” or close attachment in the araneid spider Caerostris sumatrana Strand, 1915 (Araneae: Araneidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8094444>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8094448>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8094460> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8094444>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–9. Caerostris sumatrana, female (1–4) and male (5–9). 1, 5, Habitus, dorsal. 6, Same, ventral. 2, 7, Same, anterior. 8, Same, lateral. 3, Femur, lateral. 4, 9, Metatarsus IV, lateral and dorsal. Scale bars, 1 mm. Abbreviations: Ch—carapace humps, Ep—emasculated palp, Lb—lamellar bristles." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8094444/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8094448>
    dc:description "FIGURES 10–14. Palp of Caerostris sumatrana. 10, Ventral. 11, 14, Retrolateral. 12, Prolateral. 13, Dorsal. Scale bars, 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: С—conductor, Cb—base of conductor, Ct—tip of conductor, Da—dorsal tibial apophysis, E—embolus, Eb— base of embolus, Ec—crack of embolus, So—outgrowth of subtegulum, St—subtegulum, T—tegulum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8094448/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8094460>
    dc:description "FIGURE 28. Distribution records of Caerostris spp.: C. almae (1), C. bojani (2), C. corticosa (3), C. cowani (4), C. darwini (5), C. ecclesiigera (6), C. extrusa (7), C. hirsuta (8), C. indica (9), C. linnaeus (10), C. mayottensis (11), C. mitralis (12), C. pero (13), C. sexcuspidata (14), C. sumatrana (15), C. tinamaze (16), C. vicina (17), C. wallacei (18)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8094460/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

